  "prompt": "Do you have a friend who likes you so much, shares every secret with you however hates your race, religion or cast? Strictly friendship not love.",
  "response": "It's possible for individuals to have complex relationships where they may appreciate and value someone as a friend while simultaneously holding prejudiced views against aspects of that person's identity, such as race, religion, or caste. This kind of dynamic can be challenging and problematic because genuine friendship is often built on respect and acceptance.\n\nIn a healthy friendship, mutual respect and understanding are key components. If someone harbors negative feelings toward your identity, it can create a tension that may undermine the friendship. It\u2019s important to evaluate whether that friendship is beneficial for you and aligns with your values. Conversations about these differences might be necessary to address any underlying issues, but if the person's views are deeply rooted and unwilling to change, it may be advisable to reconsider the friendship.",
